<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6936&amp;p=75121#p75121"><![CDATA[
What socram8888 suggested is called the PowerPak. And it uses CF because SD's SPI is far slower than CF's parallel ATA without some hardware assistance. Besides, to make something a PowerPak, even if it's just for one mapper, you still need a boot ROM and an SRAM the size of PRG ROM. Munchausen is supposed to be cheap.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Mar 04, 2011 3:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
